{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:53:08.050Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Large language models are trained to assign probabilities to the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "next token",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " given all previous tokens. Every agent completion—planning text, Python code, JSON tool calls—is produced by repeated next-token prediction until a stop condition. Understanding this loop explains sampling, hallucination, and why agents cannot \"look ahead\" during generation."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "At step "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "t"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", the model outputs logits "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "z_t \\in \\mathbb{R}^{|V|}"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " over vocabulary "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "V"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Probabilities: "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "P(x_t = w \\mid x_{<t}) = \\frac{\\exp(z_{t,w})}{\\sum_{w' \\in V} \\exp(z_{t,w')})}"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Training maximizes log "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "P(x_t \\mid x_{<t})"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for true tokens; inference samples or searches from this distribution."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agent orchestration is a loop: build prompt → model predicts tokens → parse tool call → execute → append result → predict again. Errors compound token by token. There is no separate \"plan then write\" module unless prompting or scaffolding creates one in text."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Autoregressive decode loop"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "tokens = tokenize(prompt)\nwhile not done:\n    logits = model(tokens)          # last position logits\n    probs = softmax(logits[-1] / temperature)\n    next_id = sample(probs)         # or argmax / top-p\n    tokens.append(next_id)\n    if next_id == EOS or len(tokens) > max_tokens:\n        break"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prefill vs decode"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prefill processes the prompt in one (or chunked) forward pass. Decode repeats single-token steps, each attending to all prior tokens. Agent latency often dominated by long prefill (big context) plus many decode steps (verbose reasoning)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Unified objective for pre-training, fine-tuning, and inference"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Flexible output—same head produces prose, code, or JSON"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Logprobs expose confidence for validation and reranking"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Greedy decoding can loop or be dull; sampling adds variance"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "No built-in backtracking—wrong early tokens hard to recover"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Each token requires a full forward pass through the stack at decode"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agentic AI connection"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Structured tool calls rely on the model continuing valid JSON token by token. Constrained decoding and grammar masks restrict "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "P(x_t)"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to legal continuations—implementing agent reliability on top of raw next-token prediction."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Expecting deterministic agents without fixed seed and temperature 0"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Ignoring that \"thinking\" tokens consume the same budget as answers"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Parsing incomplete JSON before generation finishes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "LLM generation = repeated softmax over vocabulary, one token at a time"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Training teaches "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "inlineMath",
                    "attrs": {
                      "latex": "P(x_t \\mid x_{<t})"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "; agents run this loop with tools in context"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prefill and decode have different performance profiles"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Constraints and validators compensate for greedy errors in tool JSON"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
